SIMPLE: mechanic
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mechanic
<hw>Me*chan"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>m⟦eacute⟧canique</ets> mechanics. See <er>Mechanic</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The art of the application of the
laws of motion or force to construction.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A mechanician; an artisan; an artificer; one who
practices any mechanic art; one skilled or employed in shaping and
uniting materials, as wood, metal, etc., into any kind of structure,
machine, or other object, requiring the use of tools, or instruments.
Also, a technician who maintains or repairs machinery; <as>as, an auto
<ex>mechanic</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>An art quite lost with our <qex>mechanics</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir
T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mechanic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mechanic
<hw>Me*chan"ic</hw> <pr>(m⟦esl⟧*k⟦acr⟧n"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>m⟦eacute⟧canique</ets>, L. <ets>mechanicus</ets>, Gr.
<grk>mhchaniko`s</grk>, fr. <grk>mhchanh`</grk> a machine. See
<er>Machine</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having to do with the
application of the laws of motion in the art of constructing or making
things; of or pertaining to mechanics; mechanical; <as>as, the
<ex>mechanic</ex> arts</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧These <xex>mechanic</xex>
philosophers.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Ray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Mechanic</qex> slaves,⟦br⟧
With greasy aprons, rules, and hammers.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a mechanic or artificer, or to
the class of artisans; hence, rude; common; vulgar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To make a god, a hero, or a king⟦br⟧
Descend to a <qex>mechanic</qex> dialect.</q>
<rj><qau>Roscommon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sometimes he ply'd the strong, <qex>mechanic</qex> tool.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Base.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Whitlock.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mechanical</ent>⟦br⟧
